Breda #9122
Do you have a bird’s-eye view? Are you a natural at coordinating activities and people? Are you an excellent communicator? And do you have an extensive experience in planning and managing projects and budgets? Then this is your chance to a new challenge!
De organisatie
Driscoll’s story begins in 1870, when Joseph “Ed” Reiter and Dick Driscoll started growing their very first strawberries in California. The combination of sunlight, water, love, and a lot of attention made for the most delicious fruits they had ever tasted. Soon they also started producing raspberries, blackberries, and blueberries under Driscoll’s label, a name that has become known as a real quality mark.
Driscoll’s is now the global market leader for fresh strawberries, blueberries, raspberries, and blackberries. With more than 100 years of farming heritage and hundreds of independent growers around the world, Driscoll’s is passionate about growing fresh, beautiful, and delicious berries. Their values of passion, humility, and trustworthiness have guided their mission to delight consumers around the world.
Driscoll’s exclusive patented berry varieties are developed through years of research using only natural breeding methods – meaning, no GMOs. From farm-to-table, they focus on delivering a high-quality, premium berry experience with their many supply chain partners. Driscoll’s is the trusted brand for Only the Finest Berries.
It is their mission to make everyone love soft fruit! They want nothing more than to be the world’s most beloved soft fruit company and to positively impact the lives of everyone they touch.
How do they want to do this? By following the values closest to their hearts. This means that they take care of their people, society, and the environment. They threaten their partners in a respectful way, they are open to learning from each other and they are transparent.
De functie
The Information Services Program Manager assumes responsibility for leading and managing strategic and complex IS-related projects and programs including the upcoming Global ERP Replacement. This role will be part of Driscoll’s IS Project Management team that supports the global enterprise in the planning & execution of the project portfolio.
The IS Program Manager is a strategic partner for the Business in developing the governance and roadmaps that will deliver long-term business objectives through key transformational IS programs and projects and Enterprise Business Applications. You will develop and execute project plans for multiple, simultaneous mid to large-scale projects as well as programs during all phases of the project lifecycle and partner with all IS teams, Driscoll’s business units and vendors/partners to provide excellent service and deliver quality projects on time and within budget.
Your team consists of IS Project Managers (Employees and/or Contract) reporting directly to you and will be responsible for ensuring their adherence to the standard project practices as mandated by Information Services project governance.
Some responsibilities:
Mentor and manage program teams of multiple project managers and business analysts;
Communicate consistently to the project team and stakeholders how the delivery of the projects and programs supports the business strategy and objectives;
Manage activities in collaboration with IS and Business Leadership to accomplish planned transformational implementations of Enterprise Business Applications;
Develop and maintain productive working relationships with external vendors, business partners and internal IS teams;
Develop and manage project management plans, schedules and budgets and provide consistent and comprehensive project updates, ongoing cost analysis, risk and issue management and resolution.
Het profiel
8+ years of progressive experience in a project/program management role, preferably in a PMO environment; proven track record of delivering the most complex, larger scale, global technology projects and programs – on time and within budget;
Bachelor’s Degree in business, computer science or comparable field of study;
Experience implementing multi-regional ERP systems with an emphasis on Supply Chain functions;
PMP Certification;
Extensive experience planning and managing projects within various SDLC methodologies i.e. Agile and Waterfall;
Demonstrated ability to lead cross-functional teams to achieve project objectives and work collaboratively and cohesively in a team environment
Ability to influence through a global, multi-site matrix organization is essential
Het aanbod
An attractive compensation package in line with your experience;
26 vacations days plus the possibility to buy an additional 6 days;
Work within a dynamic and international team;
Flexibility in working place;
The opportunity to contribute to the growth of their experienced and ambitious organization;
Bonus structure based on company results;
A global company with a family heart and a scale-up vibe, with a strong mission, and great values;
Their success as a company depends on creating an enabling environment where our people are energized, motivated, and empowered to perform at their highest level;
Being part of a winning team.
